HARNESS IN ONE LOOK:
- Information Layer = what the agent may read + which tools it may call. Progressive disclosure: load only what a step needs (this is the context-rot fix). Built across Phases 0,2,3,5.
- Execution Layer = deterministic guardrails that intercept the model mid-action, convert violations to errors, push back. = exit-code wall + generator/guard loops + halt-and-surface. Built Phases 1,5.
- Validation Layer = output validation, render-diffs, tracing, human gates. Built Phases 3,4,5.
- FOUNDATION: the app's toolchain. The current window.* pile is unharnessable (nothing to validate against). The migration IS what makes the harness possible; it is not bolted on at the end.

